        <h2>Repairs & Restorations</h2>
        <p class="blurb">
It's a crying shame to chuck out favorite garments once they're showing wear. Often all that's needed is reinforcement.
A classic cyclist problem is the seat of jeans that are fine elsewhere-- using different shades of thread and a sturdy patch they can often be saved almost invisibly for years more use.
I also have a stock of antique lace,vintage buttons, etc accumulated to restore things to former glory.
Wool/mohair/plaid and tweed are especially fun to tackle
</p>
